10 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
11
12 Section 1. Section 87-2-817, MCA, is amended to read:
13 "87-2-817. Licenses for service members. (1) A veteran or a disabled member of the armed forces
14 who meets the qualifications in 87-2-803(9) as a result of a combat-connected injury may apply at a fish,
15 wildlife, and parks office for a regular Class A-3 deer A tag, a Class A-4 deer B tag, a Class B-7 deer A tag, a
16 Class B-8 deer B tag, and a special antelope license made available under 87-2-506(3) for one-half of the
17 license fee. Licenses issued to veterans or disabled members of the armed forces under this part do not count
18 against the number of special antelope licenses reserved for people with permanent disabilities, as provided in
19 87-2-706.
20 (2) (a) A Montana resident who is a member of the Montana national guard or the federal reserve
21 as provided in 10 U.S.C. 10101 or who was otherwise engaged in active duty and who participated in a
22 contingency operation as provided in 10 U.S.C. 101(a)(13) that required the member to serve at least 2 months
23 outside of the state, upon request and upon presentation of the documentation described in subsection (2)(c),
24 must be issued a free resident conservation license and a Class A resident fishing license or a Class AAA
25 resident combination sports license, which may not include a Class A-6 black bear tag, upon payment of the
26 resident base hunting license fee in 87-2-116 and the purchase of the resident aquatic invasive species
27 prevention pass pursuant to 87-2-130, in the license year that the member returns from military service or in the
28 year following the member's return, based on the member's election, and in any of the 4 years after the
